                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "Innovative industrial enterprises are industrial enterprises that introduced at least one product or business process innovation (new or improved product or new or improved business process) to the market in the period under review - until 2018 - process innovation (new or significantly improved product or new or significantly improved process).Expenditures on innovation activities in enterprises by type of innovation activity are all expenses on product innovations in business processes (until 2015 process (current and investment) innovations), regardless of the source of financing, incurred in the reporting year, for work completed successfully (i.e. implementation of the innovation), unfinished (continued) and interrupted or abandoned.",
                      
